!!! Most Esperanto words start from roots and become all other parts of speech by their affixes
!!! Example: manĝ- (-i, "to eat." -o, "food." -a, "like food" [adjectival])

!!! mal-san-ul-ej-estr-aĉ-in-o-j-n. 
!!! opposite-health-person-place-boss-detestable-female-noun-plural-accusative
!!! (((opposite-health-person)-place)-(boss-detestable-female)-noun-plural-accusative)
!!! "detestable hospital matrons (Acc)"
!!! So, for the form of a stem:
!!! (prefixes)+(stem)+(postfixes)+(another prefixes-stem-postfixes)+(grammatical ending)

!prefixes.lexc
!stems/roots.lexc
!postfixes.lexc 
!grammatical_endings.lexc (noun endings, adjective endings, adverb endings, verb endings

Multichar_Symbols
+R !Root

!Parts of speech (POS)
+V  !Verb
    +Past   !Past
    +Pres   !Present
    +Fut    !Future
    +Inf    !Infinitive
    +Imp    !Imperative

+Adv !Adverb

+N !Noun
    +Sing   ! Singular
    +Plu    !Plural
        +Nom !Nominative
        +Acc !Accusative

+Adj !Adjective - also takes number and case

LEXICON R

